## 2026-05-31 — M6 Payout Disbursement (app layer)

Branch: feat/m6-payout-disbursement. Spec: docs/m6/payout-disbursement-spec.md.

### Migration integrity fix (version collision)
- The payout migration was authored as 20260531000001 but refund (merged to main
  first, PR #71) already holds 20260531000001_refund_reconcile.sql and
  20260531000002_fix_reconcile_refund_status_cast.sql. Renamed the payout
  migration to 20260531000003_m6_payout_disbursement.sql. Verified the collision
  meant the payout objects NEVER landed: a direct pg probe of the live Sydney DB
  showed zero of disburse_payout/void_payout/release_holds/organiser_available_balance,
  stripe_payout_id still NOT NULL, and no initiated_by/reversed_at columns.
- Applied 20260531000003 via `supabase db push --linked` from this worktree.
  Re-probe confirmed all four functions live with correct signatures,
  stripe_payout_id nullable, initiated_by + reversed_at added, version recorded.

### App layer (this PR, backend-only per spec)
- src/lib/payments/payout.ts (new): createPayout (reads org stripe_account_id,
  reads the REAL connected-account Stripe available balance as a hard cap, claims
  via disburse_payout, creates the Stripe payout ON the connected account with
  idempotency_key = payout id, back-fills stripe_payout_id + status in_transit,
  voids via void_payout on any failure), voidPayoutById, runReserveRelease.
  Mirrors refund.ts/connect-ledger.ts. 13 unit tests.
- src/app/api/webhooks/stripe/route.ts: payout.paid sets status=paid + arrival_date
  (NO paid_at column on payouts; arrival_date is the settlement timestamp), and is
  the source of truth for terminal success. payout.failed/canceled call void_payout
  to compensate the ledger; on a void failure the handler throws WebhookProcessingError
  and the POST returns HTTP 500 so Stripe redelivers (void_payout is idempotent via
  reversed_at, so the retry is a safe no-op). Platform-initiated rows are finalised by
  stripe_payout_id; the Phase-1 external-payout path is preserved.
- src/app/api/cron/payout-holds-release/route.ts (new, CRON_SECRET-gated, hourly):
  calls runReserveRelease -> release_holds(). Added to vercel.json crons.

### Verification
- Gates: tsc --noEmit 0 errors; eslint 0 errors; vitest 260/260; production build pass.
- Live E2E against the real Oragniser rows (org f6f8b30d..., available 5720,
  reserve hold 1430), Stripe TEST mode, service-role locally, all rows restored:
  38/38 assertions passed covering overpay-refused, Stripe-throws-after-claim ->
  voided + ledger restored, payout.failed -> void -> restore -> idempotent replay,
  forced reserve-hold release via the cron helper, and a REAL funded Stripe payout
  on the connected account (full 5720 disbursed, payout retrieved, second disburse
  a nothing_to_disburse no-op, payout.paid finalisation). State verified back to the
  exact snapshot afterwards.
- NOTE for founder: the live connected account acct_1TcWaWGtNOwOpaL9 is on a Stripe
  payout schedule of daily/delay_days 2, NOT manual. The locked model requires a
  MANUAL schedule so the reserve stays in the connected balance until release_holds
  matures it; on an automatic schedule Stripe will sweep available funds on its own.
  Flip every connected account to manual before live. (Also: that account's 7150 was
  still pending at test time, so available was 0 - the hard cap correctly refused a
  real payout until I funded the test balance.)

### [COORDINATION] Payout UI — Session 3 (admin) + Session 2 (email), AFTER M7 merges
Per founder decision (2026-05-31), this PR is backend-only. The payout UI is built
on top of the now-proven RPCs AFTER the M7 admin branch (feat/m7-admin-panel) merges,
in the admin tree, referencing this PR (feat/m6-payout-disbursement). Do NOT build it
in this branch — editing the admin/email/RBAC trees now recreates today's collision.

Hand-off, in the OWNING session's worktree:
- Session 3 (admin tree): admin payouts page under src/app/admin/(authed)/payouts.
  - List org balances; "Disburse" action calls a server action that uses a
    service-role client and `createPayout(adminClient, getStripeClient(), { organisationId,
    currency, amountCents?, actor: adminUserId })` from @/lib/payments/payout. Surface
    the structured failures verbatim: organisation_not_found | payouts_not_active |
    nothing_to_disburse | exceeds_available | stripe_account_not_set |
    exceeds_stripe_balance | invalid_input.
  - RBAC: add a `payouts.disburse` capability to the admin capability set and gate the
    action behind requireAdminSession + that capability (matches the M7 pattern from PR #64).
  - Audit: write an admin audit row on every disburse/void with actor, org, amount,
    payout_id, result (reuse the M7 audit helper; add a payout action type to its enum).
  - void path: admin "mark failed/cancel" tooling calls
    `voidPayoutById(adminClient, payoutId, 'failed'|'canceled', reason)`.
- Organiser balance/holds/history view (dashboard owner): read-only. available =
  SUM(organiser_balance_ledger.delta_cents) for the org+currency (organiser RLS-scoped,
  NOT the service_role organiser_available_balance RPC); holds from payout_holds; history
  from payouts. No new RPCs needed.
- Session 2 (src/lib/email): payout-sent + payout-paid email templates, sent from the
  webhook payout.paid path (or the disburse action). New template files only.

All five UI pieces depend ONLY on the four RPCs and payout.ts proven here; no further
schema work is required for them.

